<item>
            <title>[SEC-751] Set default security level</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-751</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For the paranoid among us, allow setting a default security level such as all methods require you to be logged in or of a certain role.  Ben and I briefly discussed this at the end of his presentation at the recent Java Symposium.  All methods or classes usable without being authenticated would have to be declared/annotated with IS_AUTHENTICATED_ANONYMOUSLY.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This way if a critical method is accidentally specified without any security restrictions, the default will hopefully prevent issues.  Whereas if a publicly accessible method is accidentally specified without any security restrictions, the mistake will be caught and no harm can be done.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
