                            <comment id="34959" author="luke" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2008 01:37:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You should now be able to set a default security level across your service layer using the protect-pointcut syntax with global-method-security. e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;global-method-security&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;protect-pointcut expression=&quot;execution(* com.mycom.&lt;b&gt;Service.&lt;/b&gt;(..))&quot; access=&quot;ROLE_USER&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/global-method-security&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="34997" author="luke" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2008 02:30:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m closing this as a duplicate since the functionality is effectively available through global-method-security.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="34998" author="mueller" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2008 03:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent, I look forward to trying this global-method-security setting.  Thanks Luke.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
